    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Catherine Kolb (fl. 1907-1908) was the niece of the French novelist and playwright, Honoré de Balzac's, wife, Evelina Hanska.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The







        <emph render="bold">Catherine Kolb Collection</emph> consists of a single bound volume which contains correspondence, newspaper clippings, photographs, and document facsimiles.</p>
      <p>The 12 pieces of



        <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> are mostly to Georges Cain, written between 1907 and 1908.</p>
      <p>The



        <emph render="bold">Photographs</emph> series contains a reproduction of a portrait of Balzac by Louis Boulanger and a photograph of a portrait of Balzac by Louis Giraud.</p>
      <p>The



        <emph render="bold">Published material</emph> series consists of newspaper clippings that relate to Mme. Evelina Hanska's deportment following her husband's death.</p>
      <p>Finally, the volume contains two



        <emph render="bold">Facsimiles</emph>.  The first is of "Acte de Naissance de Honoré Balzac," Balzac's birth certificate.  The second facsimile is "Fac-simile d'une épreuve imprimée de la première page du roman de 'Beatrix' avec les corrections de l'auteur," or a proof for Balzac's novel



        <emph render="italic">Beatrix</emph>, edited by the author.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>The contents of the collection are contained in a single bound volume.</p>
